SECTION 1: Project Briefing
1.1 What Banex Mall Is
Banex Mall is a shopping centre located in Lekki Phase 1, Lagos, Nigeria (Plot 1100/1101, Adetokunbo Ademola Crescent). It is a lifestyle, retail, dining, and entertainment destination that caters to Lagos's affluent, mobile-first consumer base. It houses fashion, electronics, beauty, dining, cinema, co-working, family entertainment, and event spaces under one roof.

1.2 The Platform Being Built
A mobile-first digital marketing platform — not a static website, not an e-commerce store. Its job is emotional: answer "What will I enjoy if I come today?", and translate that answer into physical foot traffic.

The platform must be:

Experience-driven, not information-driven
Visually engaging with smooth animations and interactions
A discovery engine for stores, dining, events, and promotions
Optimised for WhatsApp, phone calls, Google Maps as conversion actions
1.3 Phase 1 MVP Goals & Measurable Success Metrics
Primary Business Goal: Increase physical mall foot traffic by 20–30% within 6 months of launch.

KPI	Target
Monthly website visitors	Tracked via GA4
Bounce rate	< 50%
Average session duration	> 3 minutes
Store page views per session	> 2
Clicks on "Get Directions"	Tracked weekly
Promotion engagement rate	Tracked weekly
Event interaction rate	Tracked weekly
Scroll depth	> 60% on homepage
Page load time	< 3.5 seconds
Lighthouse mobile score	> 80
1.4 What Is Explicitly Out of Scope (Phase 1)
Full e-commerce marketplace
Native iOS or Android application
User accounts / registration / login
Loyalty and rewards points system
Online payments of any kind
Advanced tenant management tools / CMS
Admin dashboard (CRUD for stores/events/promotions)
Push notifications
Indoor navigation / real-time wayfinding
